Upon further inspection, there are a few issues:

1. The bootstrap class `d-flex` effectively applies `display: flex`.
2. The event listener for `#resetBtn` is added inside the event listener for `#loadMore`, so a new event listener is added to `#resetBtn` every time `#loadMore` is clicked.

Steps to the solution:

1 - Stop using `style=&quot;display:`... Instead use bootstrap classes `d-none` and `d-flex`.

    &lt;div id=&quot;resetBtn&quot; class=&quot; d-flex justify-content-center&quot; style=&quot;display: none!important;&quot;&gt;

Becomes

    &lt;div id=&quot;resetBtn&quot; class=&quot;d-none justify-content-center&quot;&gt;

2 - Move `#resetBtn` event listener outside of `#loadMore` event listener.

    $(&quot;#loadMore&quot;).on(&quot;click&quot;, function (e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      $(&quot;.content:hidden&quot;).slice(0, 4).slideDown();
      if ($(&quot;.content:hidden&quot;).length == 0) {
        $(&quot;#resetBtn&quot;).show();
        $(&quot;#loadMore&quot;).addClass(&quot;hideLoadMore&quot;);
      }
      $(&quot;#resetBtn&quot;).on(&quot;click&quot;, function (e) {
        e.preventDefault();
        $(&quot;.content:visible&quot;).slice(4, 30).slideUp();
        $(&quot;#loadMore&quot;).addClass(&quot;showloadMore&quot;);
        $(this).addClass(&quot;hideResetButton&quot;);
        console.log(this);
      });
    })

Becomes

    $(&quot;#loadMore&quot;).on(&quot;click&quot;, function (e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      $(&quot;.content:hidden&quot;).slice(0, 4).slideDown();
      if ($(&quot;.content:hidden&quot;).length == 0) {
        $(&quot;#resetBtn&quot;).show();
        $(&quot;#loadMore&quot;).addClass(&quot;hideLoadMore&quot;);
      }
    })
    $(&quot;#resetBtn&quot;).on(&quot;click&quot;, function (e) {
      e.preventDefault();
      $(&quot;.content:visible&quot;).slice(4, 30).slideUp();
      $(&quot;#loadMore&quot;).addClass(&quot;showloadMore&quot;);
      $(this).addClass(&quot;hideResetButton&quot;);
      console.log(this);
    });

3 - Use `toggleClass` to remove `d-flex` and apply `d-none` and vice versa.

    $(&quot;#resetBtn&quot;).show();
    $(&quot;#loadMore&quot;).addClass(&quot;hideLoadMore&quot;);

Becomes

    // shows reset button because it is hidden at this point
    $(&quot;#resetBtn&quot;).toggleClass(&#39;d-none d-flex&#39;);
    // hides load more button because it is shown at this point
    $(&quot;#loadMore&quot;).toggleClass(&#39;d-none d-flex&#39;);

And

    $(&quot;#loadMore&quot;).addClass(&quot;showloadMore&quot;);
    $(this).addClass(&quot;hideResetButton&quot;);

Becomes

    // shows load more button because it&#39;s hidden at this point
    $(&quot;#loadMore&quot;).toggleClass(&#39;d-none d-flex&#39;);
    // hides reset button because it is shown at this point
    $(this).toggleClass(&#39;d-none d-flex&#39;);

